data.text:
Kantonen Performance History

2019-20

Cross Country (Junior): Competed in three events ... Finished 36th at The Summit League Championship ... Ran at the NCAA Midwest Regional at Oklahoma State.

Indoor (Sophomore): Did not compete.

Outdoor (Sophomore): Did not compete.

2018-19

Cross Country (Sophomore): Ran in six meets ... Earned All-Summit League honors with an 11th place finish at the Summit League Championship, running the 6K in a career-best 21:50.70 (Oct. 27) ... Was the Fighting Hawks top-finisher at the NCAA Midwest Regional, crossing the line in 85th (Nov. 9) ... Placed fifth at the Ron Pynn Classic (Oct. 13).

Indoor (Redshirt freshman): Did not compete.

Outdoor (Sophomore): Redshirted the season.

2017-18

Cross Country (Freshman): Big Sky Conference Fall All-Academic Team … Made her collegiate debut at the Big Sky Championship (Oct. 28), where she was UND’s No. 2 finisher with a time of 18 minutes, 43.9 seconds … Also ran for UND at the NCAA Midwest Regional (Nov. 10) … Earned first letter.

Indoor (Redshirted): Redshirted the indoor season.

Outdoor (Freshman): Runner-up in the 5,000 meters at the Cobber Twilight (April 25) with a time of 18:54.40 … Placed third in the same event at the Sioux City Relays (April 13) … Earned first track letter.

Before UND

A 2017 graduate of Park Rapids Area High School … Won five letters in track and four in cross country … State participant in both cross country and track.

Personal

Majoring in mathematics and Honors … Daughter of Lee and Laurie Kantonen.
